==English==

===Noun===
'''gat'''
# ''Archaic slang, old westerns:'' A Gatling gun.
# ''Modern slang, hip-hop slang:'' Any type of gun though usually in reference to a pistol.
#:Example:  If this guy don't step off I'll blast his ass wit' my gat.

===Verb===
# ''Modern slang (Irish - North Kerry circa 1989):  Forms: 1 gating, gatting: " Used in the progressive tense i.e. Gating or Gatting;  primarily with the verb "to go"  . 1. To set out to drink ([[alcohol]]) with the intention of getting drunk. 
#:Example: Lets get a [[flagon]] of [[cider]] and go gatting tonight.

